---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import Comments from '../../../components/Comments.astro';
import { BASE_PATH } from '../../../config';

const starterTrack = [
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/headings`, title: 'Headings', desc: 'Build the information hierarchy before worrying about polish.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/lists`, title: 'Lists', desc: 'Steps, requirements, tasks, and summaries all rely on lists.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/links`, title: 'Links', desc: 'Connect context, references, commands, and related pages.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/code`, title: 'Code', desc: 'Protect commands, configs, and examples from being mangled by prose.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/paragraphs`, title: 'Paragraphs', desc: 'Control reading rhythm instead of shipping one giant wall of text.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/emphasis`, title: 'Emphasis', desc: 'Give extra weight to warnings, conclusions, and key decisions.' },
];

const supportTopics = [
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/blockquotes`, title: 'Blockquotes', desc: 'Useful when you need callouts, notes, or quoted source material.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/horizontal-rules`, title: 'Horizontal Rules', desc: 'Use them when sections need separation, not by default everywhere.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/images`, title: 'Images', desc: 'Add this when screenshots and diagrams become necessary.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/line-breaks`, title: 'Line Breaks', desc: 'Important to understand, but not a first-day priority.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/escaping-characters`, title: 'Escaping', desc: 'Most useful when teaching syntax or showing raw characters.' },
  { href: `${BASE_PATH}/en/basic/htmls`, title: 'HTML Tags', desc: 'Reach for this only when plain Markdown is not expressive enough.' },
];
---

<Layout title="High-Frequency Markdown Basics" lang="en">
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="section section-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-wider uppercase text-[var(--color-terracotta)] mb-4">
            High-frequency syntax
          </p>
          <h1 class="font-serif-display text-[var(--text-inverse)] mb-6">
            Learn These 6 Markdown Patterns First
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-[var(--text-on-dark)] opacity-80" style="line-height: 1.6;">
            If your goal is to write clearer READMEs, issues, and project notes, you do not need the entire syntax catalog on day one.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-12">
          <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
            <div class="card sticky top-24">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
                Recommended order
              </h3>
              <nav class="space-y-2">
                {starterTrack.map((topic, index) => (
                  <a
                    href={topic.href}
                    class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] hover:text-[var(--color-terracotta)] py-1"
                  >
                    <span class="inline-flex w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-[var(--bg-muted)] text-[var(--text-primary)] items-center justify-center text-xs flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                      {index + 1}
                    </span>
                    <span>{topic.title}</span>
                  </a>
                ))}
              </nav>

              <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--border-default)]">
                <h4 class="font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Add later as needed</h4>
                <div class="space-y-2">
                  {supportTopics.map((topic) => (
                    <a href={topic.href} class="block text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] hover:text-[var(--color-terracotta)]">
                      {topic.title}
                    </a>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </aside>

          <div class="lg:col-span-3">
            <div class="prose">
              <h2>If you only have 30 minutes today</h2>
              <p>Do not try to memorize the entire Markdown surface area. For READMEs, collaboration notes, project docs, and lightweight knowledge bases, only a handful of syntax patterns show up constantly. Learn those first and your writing improves immediately.</p>

              <h2>Start with these 6</h2>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Headings</strong>: they create the structure that makes scanning possible.</li>
                <li><strong>Lists</strong>: they carry steps, tasks, requirements, and summaries.</li>
                <li><strong>Links</strong>: they connect references, related pages, and context.</li>
                <li><strong>Code</strong>: they preserve commands, configuration, and examples accurately.</li>
                <li><strong>Paragraphs</strong>: they control pacing and keep content readable.</li>
                <li><strong>Emphasis</strong>: they highlight what truly matters instead of shouting everywhere.</li>
              </ul>

              <h2>When to learn the rest</h2>
              <p>Images, blockquotes, escaping, horizontal rules, and inline HTML all have their place, but they are rarely the bottleneck on day one. Add them when your actual documents demand them.</p>

              <h2>What a “good enough” Markdown document should contain</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>A clear heading structure that a reader can scan in seconds.</li>
                <li>Just enough lists to organize steps and decisions.</li>
                <li>Accurate links and code blocks so instructions stay trustworthy.</li>
                <li>Minimal but deliberate emphasis for warnings, conclusions, and key actions.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-10">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6">
                Learn these first
              </h3>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                {starterTrack.map((topic) => (
                  <a href={topic.href} class="card group hover:shadow-whisper transition-all hover:border-[var(--color-terracotta)]">
                    <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2 group-hover:text-[var(--color-terracotta)]">
                      {topic.title}
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">
                      {topic.desc}
                    </p>
                  </a>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-10">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6">
                Add these when the job calls for them
              </h3>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                {supportTopics.map((topic) => (
                <a href={topic.href} class="card group hover:shadow-whisper transition-all hover:border-[var(--color-terracotta)]">
                  <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2 group-hover:text-[var(--color-terracotta)]">
                    {topic.title}
                  </h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">
                    {topic.desc}
                  </p>
                </a>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Comments slug="basic" />
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
